node.text:
The fake fitfluencers makes a killing convincing people they are broken, that their metabolism isn't functioning, that they eat too little to lose weight (wtf), and is just missing what they can provide:

That ONE thing.
That ONE diet.
That ONE pill.
That ONE routine.
That ONE product.

But here's the truth: There isn't *ONE* thing, and you're NOT broken. You probably just need to lift, eat like an adult, move around more and be patient.

Happy Monday and week ahead gals and doods

#patience #lies #liftheavy #healthyhabits #itsalifestyle

node.text:
Reklame

One of the hardest things you can do as a
woman is show up as your whole self, because we always gets judged upon our look's, body, glam and personality. The reason for that being, is people feel intimidated by women who are comfortable with who they are. Truth is that the more you that you become, the less chance there is of everyone liking you.

You have to remember that the goal isn't to have everyone liking you, the goal is to like yourself.

Happy Weekend.

#knowyourworth #believeinyourself #youareenough #standtall

node.text:
Adam Moserri

Is the CEO of Instagram, and he broke the news himself : Instagram is no longer a photosharing app.

So, forget growth of reach and engagement from now on, Instagram is turning into a video and shortclip competitor to TikTok, and in the future YouTube, by basicly giving people who wants to deliver a message via captions and beautiful images the middle finger.

Posting pictures, writing captions, being creative in front, and behind the camera, will no longer be "rewarded", so now you know why your reach, engagement and exposure have dropped dramatically the past few weeks. Of course there's more to it than this simplified caption, and if you didn't see the videolink by @thechrishau I posted in my stories yesterday, go checkout his video on YouTube where he goes into depth with what's up/down in all of this change Instagram is going through.

So, going forward from here is going to be a challenge, but a challenge is always welcoming, and threading new waters always brings new opportunies, so let's cheer to that, guess I have to make a lot more video material from now on.

Happy Tuesday

#movingon #moveon
#changes #embrace #believeinyourself

node.text:
Let this sink in -

Youre always one decision away from living a different life. Maybe it's exaggerated a bit, but the choice is yours and yours alone.

And I made that one life changing decision more than 10 years ago - After struggling in a bad relationship, as a 22 year old I grabbed my son and left my ex, I was broke, obese, depressed, had no job and nowhere to live, I had to woman up and do what was best for me and my son, and it took me years to settle and find a way to make it work.

The morale of the story: I made it, I stood up for myself and left everything except my son behind. The bad habits, weight issues, no self esteem, toxic friendships and the unhealthy lifestyle got the middle finger as time went by.

And here we are, and what a journey, lesson and change of life it has been, not regretting a thing because my kids are happy, my husband is happy and im happy.

Dreams become real.

#dreamscometrue #believeinyourself #lifechanging #proudmom #quads #itsuptoyou

node.text:
Swipe through, and remind yourself why you should NEVER compare your personal story to someone's online prescence.

You know what, bodies look different depending on lights, poses, age, weight, and a dozen other things. Online shows a single perfect moment from millions of strangers, it's their moment of shine, and that's wonderful and empowering and all dandy. But offline, we get more of what's real, the folds, scars, thingies, breakups, beating, surgeries, heart breaks, hangovers, sickness, low self esteem and crumbling of self confidence.

So again, don't measure yourself by some stranger on the internet. You're doing just fine.

Happy Thursday sweet souls

PS. That first picture was to catch your attention obviously.

#perfectlyimperfect #scars #therealdeal #believeinyourself #itsnatural

node.text:
Tips to grow your Instagram

There arent any! Ive been in here for +6 years now, and the good old days of growth is long gone, Instagram isnt what it used to be, its nearly impossible to stand out since its saturated with millions of people doing the same thing.

Don't listen whenever you stumble upon an influencer saying they beat the algorithm, and you should follow their steps for instagrowth, it's bullshit. Just take one look at Instagrams own account, and you'll see they have below average reach themselves, and if anyone should know how to have a massive reach, it would be them, right?

When that being said, here's my personal tips to have a great account in here: Be real, be kind, be positive, be transparent, be honest, be supportive, post regularly, dont pretend to be someone you're not, write meaningful captions, take great photos, reply to relevant comments/questions, focus on your thing, hand out compliments and just like most other things in life, have fun with it.

Happy Midweek

node.text:
Things to remember

1. Nobody expects you to be a 100%, so neither should you. We are just mere human beings, not world class athletes. It's way more sustainable, and healthy, to follow something 80% than 100%, you'll just set yourself up for failure if you constantly aim to be at 100%.

2. Dont feel guilty or sorry for slipping on your diet for a couple of days, just pick up where you left and keep going. The more you restrict yourself from joy and actually living balanced, the more you will screw up.

3. Focus on what's actually achieveable and within reach, hip dips, cellulite and losing weight fast should be the last thing that crosses your mind. Building strength, muscle, living balanced and having an active (doesnt mean cardio) life is healthy for you now, and in the years to come.

Happy Motivation Monday
